<div class="modal fade" id="placement-help-modal" tabindex="-1">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-xl">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title">Placement phase</h5>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <h6>When is it?</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small">The placement phase runs for a limited time — exact dates will be shown here soon. Place your barrio before it closes!</p>

                <div class="row g-4">

                    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <img src="~/img/barrio-map/barrio-draw.png" class="card-img-top" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: contain; object-position: top;" alt="Drawing a barrio" />
                            <div class="card-body p-2">
                                <h6 class="card-title mb-1">Placing your barrio</h6>
                                <p class="card-text text-muted small mb-0">Click <strong>Add my barrio on the map</strong> to start drawing. Then click on the map to drop points that define your space — each click adds a corner. Close the shape by clicking back on the first point.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <img src="~/img/barrio-map/barrio-edit.png" class="card-img-top" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: contain; object-position: top;" alt="Editing a barrio shape" />
                            <div class="card-body p-2">
                                <h6 class="card-title mb-1">Adjusting the shape</h6>
                                <ul class="card-text text-muted small ps-3 mb-0">
                                    <li>Drag a corner point to move it</li>
                                    <li>Drag the whole shape to reposition it</li>
                                    <li>Click the midpoint of an edge (where the length in metres is shown) to add a new corner</li>
                                    <li>Click a point to select it (it turns orange), then press <kbd>Delete</kbd> or <kbd>Backspace</kbd> to remove it</li>
                                    <li>The area in m² is shown in the centre and updates as you edit</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <img src="~/img/barrio-map/barrio-history.png" class="card-img-top" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: contain; object-position: top;" alt="History of a barrio" />
                            <div class="card-body p-2">
                                <h6 class="card-title mb-1">Saving &amp; editing later</h6>
                                <p class="card-text text-muted small mb-0">Happy with it? Hit <strong>Save</strong>. Afterwards, click your barrio on the map to see its size, then <strong>Edit</strong> to jump back into edit mode. Every save creates a history entry — use the <strong>History</strong> button to browse and restore any previous version: hit the preview button to show the version, and then save the one you want to restore. No stress, you can't break anything!</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <img src="~/img/barrio-map/barrio-out-of-zone.png" class="card-img-top" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: contain; object-position: top;" alt="Invalid placement" />
                            <div class="card-body p-2">
                                <h6 class="card-title mb-1">Stay inside the white zones</h6>
                                <p class="card-text text-muted small mb-0">The dashed white areas mark the safe camping zones, protected by lightning poles. <strong>Camping outside them is not allowed</strong>, so keep your barrio inside those boundaries.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <img src="~/img/barrio-map/barrio-overlap.png" class="card-img-top" style="max-height: 250px; object-fit: contain; object-position: top;" alt="Overlap of two barrios" />
                            <div class="card-body p-2">
                                <h6 class="card-title mb-1">Overlaps? Talk it out!</h6>
                                <p class="card-text text-muted small mb-0">If your barrio overlaps with another, reach out on <a href="https://discord.com/channels/1462886445583962245/1467793922074873896" target="_blank" class="text-decoration-none">Discord #city-planning</a> and work it out together. If there are unresolved conflicts at the end of the phase, the city planning team will sort them out.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                        <div class="card h-100">
                            <div class="card-body p-2">
                                <h6 class="card-title mb-1">Colours &amp; sound zones</h6>
                                <p class="card-text text-muted small mb-0">Each barrio is coloured by its preferred sound zone (editable from your barrio page).</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
